headline: Home Depot earnings, housing data, Fed remarks: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Tuesday, Aug. 19. Home Depot (HD), Viking Holdings (VIK), and Toll Brothers (TOL) will report quarterly results. Home Depot will announce its second quarter results in the morning, with analysts anticipating a 2% rise in same-store sales. Data for July housing starts and building permits will be out in the morning, as economists forecast housing starts to decrease slightly and building permits to hold steady from the previous month. Federal Reserve Vice Chair for Supervision Michelle Bowman will deliver remarks. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
